</P>
<P>
   _ Julius Caesar (Rex Harrison) to Cleopatra in ``Cleopatra''
</P>
<P>
   MARRIAGE
</P>
<P>
   ``Women are a nuisance. At first you suffer because you want a
wife. Then you suffer because you're jealous. And when your
jealousy is past you end up suffering because she bosses you
around.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Ulysses (Gabriele Antonini) in ``Hercules''
</P>
<P>
   ``Hercules, that ceremony you went through _ the bonds of
matrimony. Now you're married. So drive carefully!''
</P>
<P>
   _ Ulysses in ``Hercules Unchained''
</P>
<P>
   ``One wife? One God, that I can understand _ but one wife? That
is not civilized. It is not generous.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Sheikh Ilderim (Hugh Griffith) in ``Ben-Hur'' (MCMLIX)
</P>
<P>
   nn
</P>
<P>
   FAITH
</P>
<P>
   ``Your tricks won't work on me because I know them! Tell that to
Jesus the next time you see Him!''
</P>
<P>
   _ Demetrius in ``Demetrius and the Gladiators''
</P>
<P>
   ``If I was to punish every blasphemy, I would have no
followers.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Zeus (Niall MacGinnis) in ``Jason and the Argonauts (MCMLXIII)
</P>
<P>
   Demetrius: ``Get it from her!''
</P>
<P>
   The Apostle Peter (Michael Rennie): ``How?''
</P>
<P>
   Demetrius: ``How should I know? One of your miracles!''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Demetrius and the Gladiators''
</P>
<P>
   DEATH
</P>
<P>
   ``Petronius? Dead? By his own hand? I don't believe it. I shall
never forgive him for this. Never. Without my permission? It's
rebellion! It's blasphemy!''
</P>
<P>
   _ Nero in ``Quo Vadis''
</P>
<P>
   ``You're almost dead! What's it like?''
</P>
<P>
   _ Caligula to Nerva (John Gielgud), who has opened his veins, in
``Caligula''
</P>
<P>
   ``You know, it's quite possible, Octavian, that when you die,
you will die without ever having been alive.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Marc Antony (Richard Burton) in ``Cleopatra''
</P>
<P>
   ETERNAL TRUTHS
</P>
<P>
   ``The worst sort of life is better than the best kind of
death.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Glydon (William Marshall) in ``Demetrius and the Gladiators''
</P>
<P>
   ``When the truth is ugly, only a lie can be beautiful.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Messalina in ``Demetrius and the Gladiators''
</P>
<P>
   Marc Antony: ``Queens, queens. Strip them naked as any other
woman, they are no longer queens.''
</P>
<P>
   Rufio (Martin Landau): ``It is also difficult to tell the rank
of a naked general.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Cleopatra''
</P>
<P>
   Sources: the Internet Movie Database (www.imdb.com); ``The Movie
Quote Book,'' by Harry Haun (Lippincott &AMP; Crowell, 1980); ``Film
Quotations,'' by Robert A. Nowlan and Gwendolyn W. Nowlan
(McFarland, 1994); and the local video store.
</P>
