<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SYDNEY-UPDATE _ SYDNEY, Australia _ A special report on how
Sydney is prepared to handle the 2000 Olympic Games. There have
been minor controversies about tickets, housing, etc., but the
venues are complete and the city appears ready for business.
(Auchmutey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-BRAVES _ ATLANTA _ Coverage of the Philadelphia Phillies at
Atlanta Braves. (Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: First pitch is at 7:10 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   BBC-NCAA-BATS _ That ringing metallic sound you hear in the
corner of the dugout is coming from college baseball players trying
to find out which bat in the rack is ``hot.'' The NCAA-aluminum bat
controversy in college baseball won't go away. Last year, the NCAA
set guidelines to bat manufacturers on how ``lively'' bats could
be. The rule, which went into effect this year, sparked lawsuits
from Easton and others. Now, bat makers are complaining that some
companies found a ``loophole'' and that at least one of the bats on
the market remains ``hot.'' That has power hitters searching for
the ultimate Hotbat as college baseball heads into its title
season. (Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
