   The stories are slugged BC-CNS-keyword and move in the ``l''
news category. They are edited by adjunct professors who work at
The New York Times, Daily News, Newsday, The New York Post, The
Wall Street Journal and The Associated Press, among other places.
The stories are written by master's degree candidates at the
Graduate School of Journalism at Columbia University. All we ask is
that you send us a tearsheet.
</P>
<P>
   So please, if you can, use our stories. Most of them are news
features that can be held until you have a pesky hole to fill.
