<P>
   CLINTON-TWILIGHT _ WASHINGTON _ He takes Air Force One around
the globe, jetting into foreign capitals to be feted as the senior
statesman of world politics and power. He draws rock-star welcomes
around his own country, where he can generate $1 million for a
fellow Democrat with a ten-minute speech at a political fundraising
event. He taunts his congressional foes _ those still left standing
_ with charges that their bid to impeach him threatened the
Constitution. Clinton is openly relishing the Indian Summer of his
political life, those final golden months before the August
political conventions usher him into the autumn of irrelevance.
(Deans).
