<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-HEAT _ The New York Knicks and Miami Heat have become
two of the most hated rivals in the NBA. In addition to playing in
the same division, the teams have met in the playoffs the last
three years and the games have been highlighted by fights between
players (P.J. Brown and Charlie Ward, Larry Johnson and Alonzo
Mourning) and verbal wars between coaches Pat Riley and Jeff Van
Gundy. The series have always been hard-fought, with the Knicks
winning last season on Allan Houston's last-second shot in the
deciding game of the first round. The team met in the Eastern
Conference semifinals beginning Sunday in Miami and it figures to
be another classic matchup between rivals. (Bunn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
