<HEADER>
A8041 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r s BC-BKN-FREE-THROWS-TEX     05-06 1109
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-FREE-THROWS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AS SHAQ CAN TELL YOU, NOTHING'S FREE FROM THE LINE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   He wears a tattoo of Superman on his arm. But when Shaquille
O'Neal looks at his woeful free-throw percentage, he knows it is
his kryptonite.
</P>
<P>
   Basketball's equivalent of the extra point and the open-netter,
free throws are supposed to be a reward. But for some of the NBA's
best players, shots from the line are anything but free. Especially
for Shaq.
</P>
<P>
   They are the lone weak spot in O'Neal's dynamic game, rendering
him powerless at times. Because of his career free-throw percentage
of .534, some opponents opt to foul him late in close games. His
career playoff percentage, .520, is even worse and his struggles at
the line might hurt the Lakers in their hunt for the NBA title so
many were prepared to hand them at the end of the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's the only `but' I've got in my life,'' he said.
``Perfect movies. Perfect low-post game. Perfect life. `But, you're
not a good free-throw shooter.' I'll always hear it.''
</P>
<P>
   In the NBA playoffs that is a big ``but''.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers entered their first-round playoff series toting one
of the best regular-season records in NBA history, and were
supposed to make short work of the Sacramento Kings. ``But/ ... the
Kings forced the Lakers to a deciding fifth game. The Lakers held
on to win the series with a 113-86 victory Friday night, but the
Lakers' inconsistent free-throw shooting was a big reason the Kings
pushed the Lakers to the limit.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings shot 75 percent from the line and scored 23 percent of
their points on free throws in the series. O'Neal, who leads the
Lakers in scoring average at 29.7 points per game, made 11 of 23
free throws in the Lakers' three victories, but made only 10 of 26
in the two games the Lakers lost in the series. He shot 52.4
percent during the regular season, down from the 54 percent he shot
last year and the 52.7 percent he made two years ago. However, it's
a stark improvement from the 48.7 and 48.4 percentages he converted
during the 1995-'96 and '96-'97 seasons. Translation: the more you
send Shaq to the line, the better chance you have to beat him.
</P>
<P>
   So what does Superman do about the kryptonite? Practice, you
say?
</P>
<P>
   Lakers coach Phil Jackson, he of the Zen philosophy, said
free-throw shooting is a principle that consists of more than just
practice, practice, practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``Some of it's mechanical, but most of it is psychological and
rhythm,'' Jackson said. ``\RO'Neal's\S doing a whole different
rhythm thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not like every shot he takes is different. Now every shot
he's taking has the same semblance of order to it. That's real
important that at least you get consistent, so you can practice the
same thing.''
</P>
<P>
   Maybe Superman could take a lesson from Utah's Swishman.
</P>
<P>
   Utah guard Jeff Hornacek has been almost automatic at the
free-throw line. This year Hornacek led the NBA in free-throw
shooting as he only missed nine of 180 attempts. His .950
percentage is the NBA's third all-time single-season mark.
</P>
<P>
   Hornacek has never shot under .822 from the line since a .777
mark as a rookie for the 1986-87 season. Hornacek's free-throw
shooting routine consists of stepping to the line, wiping the right
side of his face three times _ that's his way of saying hi to his
three kids _ dribbling three times, and bending his knee three
times before releasing the ball.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's got great concentration, and he's always been very
good,'' Jazz coach Jerry Sloan said. ``Any player with that kind of
concentration, there's always a chance he could go a long way
without missing.''
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this season], Hornacek made 67 consecutive free throws
before missing one Jan. 6 against the Mavericks at Reunion Arena.
</P>
<P>
   About six years ago, Hornacek used a tip from a psychology tape
that helped increase his percent made from the mid-80s to the
upper-80s.
</P>
<P>
   ``I envision my whole routine first, then I envision the shot
going in the basket and then I actually go through my routine,'' he
said. ``Since then I've been up near that 90 range.''
</P>
<P>
   Gary Boren, the free-throw shooting coach for the Mavericks,
said O'Neal's free-throw woes can be corrected with time, patience,
practice and change of habits.
</P>
<P>
   ``The No. 1 problem with Shaq is he shoots a line-drive free
throw,'' Boren said. ``Nobody's going to tip that hoop toward him.
He's got to get some arc on it, so he'll have a target to shoot
at.''
</P>
<P>
   Boren said free-throw shooting is all about mechanics first, and
then it's mental, balance and muscle memory.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's an athletic happening, like hitting a baseball or hitting
a golf ball,'' he said. ``There are certain things that are common
to all athletic happenings like that.''
</P>
<P>
   The National Basketball Coaches Association recently did a
10-year study of 3,500 NCAA Division I men's college games. It
discovered that 25 percent of all points scored during that time
were from the free-throw line, 35 percent of all the points scored
in last five minutes were from the free-throw line, and 67 percent
of all the points scored by the winning team in the last minute
were from the line.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've done my own tracking, and those numbers track pretty much
the same in the pros,'' said Boren, who has been an NBA free-throw
specialist coach for seven years. ``Free throws are extremely
important.
</P>
<P>
   ``At the end of the season our guys were hitting them left and
right, and it's pretty comforting for the coaching staff to be
sitting on the bench knowing that at the end of the game if you're
ahead, you know you're going to win. And to know that you can put a
whole team out there where they all shoot over 80 percent, that's a
big advantage.''
</P>
<P>
   An advantage the Lakers don't have if Shaq is at the line.
</P>
<P>
   \Nsubheds:This season's best
</P>
