<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, May 7. If you have
any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
VEEP _ The national nominating conventions are still more than four
months away, but speculation about who might be the actual
candidates in the Republican and Democratic veepstakes has turned
to a long list of women. By KRIS MAYES. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MCCAIN _ If John McCain has his way, the leader of the Arizona
delegation to the Republican National Convention will be his
companion on the campaign trail, Cindy McCain. But the senator's
efforts have rekindled anger among supporters of Gov. Jane Hull. By
KRIS MAYES. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WATER _ If Arizona doesn't manage its water better, some of the
state's shiny new cities could dry up like the deserts they sprang
from. Growth is pushing communities across the state ever closer to
serious water crises. By SHAUN McKINNON. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COL _ The Arizona Republic (yeah, still me) has tracked
down the 21-year-old son of Ruth Ann Burns to ask if he'll be
sending his mom flowers for Mother's Day. ``What's it to you,
old-timer?'' asks the young man, whose name is Nicholas. It has to
do with what happened in court back in 2000, he's told. By E.J.
MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
